text: Robert Dillon Browne (1811 – 1 July 1850) was an Irish Repeal Association politician. Browne was elected Repeal Association MP for at a by-election in 1836—caused by the elevation of Dominick Browne to a Peerage—and held the seat until his death in 1850. ==References== ==External links== * Category:UK MPs 1835–1837 Category:UK MPs 1837–1841 Category:UK MPs 1841–1847 Category:UK MPs 1847–1852 Category:Members of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for County Mayo constituencies (1801–1922) Category:Irish Repeal Association MPs Category:1811 births Category:1850 deaths
